article.headline: Bat delays game for five minutes
article.linkText: Flying bat doesn't stop Texas Tech in Vegas
article.story:
LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Alesha Robertson scored 21 points and Chesley
Dabbs added 17 to lead No. 12 Texas Tech to an 87-53 victory over
Arkansas State in a Duel in the Desert first-round game Saturday.

Robertson connected on 5 of 6 shots during the second half, when
the Lady Raiders outscored the Lady Indians 44-25.

Texas Tech opened the second half with a 19-5 run after leading
43-28 at halftime.

Judith Smith added 12 points for Texas Tech, while Cisti
Greenwalt tallied 10 points and a team-high 12 rebounds and Erin
Grant had 10 points and a team-high six assists.

Adrianne Davie led the Lady Indians with 14 points and seven
rebounds and Rudy Sims had seven points and six assists.

The game included a 5-minute delay during the first half when a
bat took flight through the arena. Texas Tech assistant coach Roger
Reding helped capture the bat when he threw a towel over it and
stopped it from flying.
